capability.name: Brokered Product
capability.definition: This Service Domain oversees all activities associated with the coordinated delivery of 3rd party products and services
capability.role: Administer 3rd party coordination for the production delivery of 'brokered' products and services that are offered through the bank, possibly in combination with the bank's own product and service offerings
capability.example: Access to a bank approved insurance broker is facilitated by a customer's relationship manager
